/* sect1 */ "Moving, Renaming, and Deleting Shared Folders|||Moving, Renaming, and Deleting Shared Folders¶The following conditions apply for¶that you own:¶If you move a shared folder to another location in your Tempo Box folder, it remains shared for all other collaborators.¶If you move a shared folder to a location outside of your Tempo Box folder, it is no longer shared, and other collaborators cannot see it. The folder becomes a normal folder and the content is deleted from your Tempo Box folder.¶If you rename a shared folder, it is renamed for all other collaborators.¶If you delete a shared folder, it is deleted for all other collaborators.¶The following conditions apply for shared folders that you have permission to access, but do not own:¶You cannot move the root of a shared folder,¶, or¶.¶If you move a shared folder outside of your user name folder, the folder is no longer shared with you. The folder becomes a normal folder and will no longer sync. If you accidentally move the folder outside of your user name folder, you must contact the folder owner to send you a new sharing invitation.¶You cannot rename the root of a shared folder.¶If you delete a shared folder, it is only removed from your Tempo Box folder. Other collaborators can continue to access the folder. If you accidentally deleted the folder, you must contact the folder owner to send you a new sharing invitation.¶If you delete an Enterprise folder, it is only removed from your Tempo Box folder. Other collaborators can continue to access the folder. If a Content Server user accidentally deleted an Enterprise folder, they can add the folder again from the folder location in Content Server . For more information on adding Enterprise folders to your Tempo Box folder, see the¶.¶You cannot rename the root of an Enterprise folder unless you have¶Edit Permissions¶permission to the folder.¶You cannot rename or move the root of a file library in a Tempo Social community.¶|syncpc-renamedelmoveshare-bg.htm",

/* chapter */ "Creating and Managing Tasks|||Creating and Managing Tasks¶Within a folder, you can create a task for yourself or assign a task to another colleague in a shared or Enterprise folder. For example, you can add a document in a shared folder and create a task for a collaborator to review the document. When you create a task, a notification is sent to the task recipient outlining the task description and due date, if provided. The notification icon appears in the top, right pane when a task is assigned to you. If enabled, you can also receive an email notification when you are assigned a task. For details, see¶.¶The task notification will always appear regardless of the task status or even if the task is deleted.¶Folders that contain active tasks will show the task icon¶. For example,¶. The task icon disappears when the status of all of the tasks is set to¶Completed¶or¶Cancelled¶, or all of the tasks in the folder are deleted. The task icon only shows on the folders which have tasks created against them. A folder with tasks created within a subfolder will not show the task icon on the parent folder.¶|syncpcwb-tasks-so.htm",

/* sect1 */ "Viewing a Task|||Viewing a Task¶To view a task:¶In the top, right pane, click the notification icon¶and then click the task notification. The folder containing the task opens.¶You can also view a task by clicking the folder which contains the task. Folders that contain active tasks will show the task icon¶. For example,¶.¶Click¶TASKS¶in the right pane. The list of all available tasks displays.¶|syncpcwb-viewtask-p.htm",

/* sect1 */ "Creating a Task|||Creating a Task¶To create a task:¶Select a folder or add a new folder and select it. You must create a task within a folder.¶Users with read-only access to a Tempo Box shared folder or Enterprise folder cannot create tasks.¶Click¶TASKS¶in the right pane.¶Click the¶Task Description¶box and enter a description for your task. Every task that you create must have a unique description. If you are assigning a task to a collaborator, it’s best to provide a thorough description of the task and state the document(s) you want the collaborator to review. You cannot update the description after the task is created. If you want to alter the description, you need to create a new task.¶Optional¶To assign the task to a colleague, click the¶Enter Assignee Name¶box, type a colleague’s name, and select the colleague’s name from the list that appears. You can assign a task to Content Server users, Standard users, or External users as long as they have access to the folder. If you type the name of a person and the person’s name does not appear in a list, verify that the colleague is a collaborator in the folder by clicking¶COLLABORATORS¶in the right pane. You can also assign a task to yourself.¶You can only assign a task to individual users in a share or Enterprise folder. Assigning tasks to groups is not supported at this time.¶Optional¶To assign a due date, click¶and select a date. The due date must be greater than the current date. You cannot assign or update the due date after the task is created. If you want to alter the due date of a task, you need to create a new task.¶Click¶Create Task¶.¶The folder will show a task icon¶when the folder has active tasks. For example,¶. When the status of all of the tasks is set to¶Completed¶or¶Cancelled¶, the task icon disappears.¶|syncpcwb-createtask-p.htm",

/* sect1 */ "Updating the Status of a Task|||Updating the Status of a Task¶To update the status of a task:¶Select the folder that has an active task assigned to you or click the task notification icon¶.¶Folders with active tasks will show a task icon¶. For example,¶. When the status of all of the tasks is set to¶Completed¶or¶Cancelled¶, the task icon disappears.¶Click¶TASKS¶in the right pane. The list of all available tasks displays.¶Locate the task assigned to you and change the status from¶Pending¶to one of the other settings. If a task is not assigned, you can update the task status. Updating the status of an unassigned task does not assign the task to you. You cannot update the status of the tasks assigned to other users.¶|syncpcwb-updatestatus-p.htm",

/* sect1 */ "Deleting a Task|||Deleting a Task¶To delete a task:¶Select the folder containing a task that you created. You can only delete the tasks you created.¶Folders with active tasks will show a task icon¶. For example,¶. The task icon disappears when the status of all of the tasks is set to¶Completed¶or¶Cancelled¶, or all of the tasks in the folder are deleted.¶Click¶TASKS¶in the right pane. A list of tasks appears.¶Locate the task of interest and click the X in the top right corner of the task.¶|syncpcwb-deletetask-p.htm",

/* chapter */ "Configuring Settings|||Configuring Settings¶In the top, right pane, clicking your name reveals a menu where you can do the following:¶Update the photo that other users see when viewing folders that are shared with you.¶Configure OpenText Tempo Box, Content Server Edition to notify you by email whenever someone invites you to share a folder, or whenever a shared folder is updated. Your administrator must enable email notifications for you to receive them.¶View version information.¶Sign out of the Web client.¶|syncpcwb-settings-so.htm",

